title: Grateful Dead Live at Curtis Hixon Convention Hall on 1978-12-13
lineage: SBD -> Cassette Master > Cassette > Reel > Dat > CD -> EAC -> WAV
description: Passenger, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Candyman, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, It's All Over Now, Loser, Jack Straw, Deal I Need A Miracle-> Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Shakedown Street-> Black Peter-> Playin' In The Band-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: Try the other soundboard version instead Don't bother with this version of this show; follow the link to the other soundboard source instead, which is WAY better.  The sound on this one sucks; it sounds as if it's being filtered through a couple of tons of shit.  Definitely NOT recommended!

I retract my statement I wish I could go back and delete my post about Donna Godchaux.  Because I recently discovered her Kettle Joe's Psychedelic Swamp Revue project.  They're great and Donna still sounds amazing!  If you haven't heard them you should check them out!!

I Like it I almost passed on this and I'm grateful I did'nt. Keith is having a better than usual night for this period, and all else sound good to me also. Phil is nice and present. Many many thanks to GD and all who have made these shows available. Aloha
Tampa Red nailed it This is not the version you want.
